Community members are recounting harrowing details of the July unrest. eNCA reporter Silindelo Masikane has more on this story. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The July unrest was propaganda paid for by the ANC, according to an Alexandra community leader. Benjamin Chisare was testifying before the South African Human Rights Commission hearing into the July violence. READ: ANC Veterans League president: Unrest orchestrated by criminals "I made it simple to everyone that said social media showed us, we should not be foolish enough sorry for using that word to say that the drive to the of propaganda was the realise Zuma campaign, that was propaganda enough to confuse the country," he said. "That is the propaganda that they were pushing and that propaganda was funded by the ANC itself we know that, including the way it was mobilised. Hence I’m saying it's not unrest, the way it was mobilised, there are certain comrades within the ANC who -- which if I had to tell you -- we would need to be in a closed session."